						               													<description>32 cards, four of each family (color) that make it possible to play two games:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Action Game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of this game is to get rid of all your cards as soon as possible. Each player gets 5 cards and the rest go in a pile face-down with 1 card turn up next to it. In a player turn he must play a card with the same colour, number or symbol as the face-up next to the draw pile. When a card with a symbol it's played, the action related to that symbol must be performed. Then the next player goes.&amp;#10;When no card can be played, the player must take the top card from the face-down pile. If that card matches it can be played, if not the turn moves for the next player.&amp;#10;You win if get rid of all your cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Family Game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of the game is to get the most families of minions you can (4 of each colour makes a family). One player ask for a type of card to any other player. If he can form a family he displays it in front of it and can continue until one player can group all the families he has in his hand at any given moment.&amp;#10;If a player asks a card and the other player does not have it that player's turn ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
